post_text:
In recognition of our retirees, Kayla Snyder put together this video. This year has been a very interesting and especially challenging year as we try to find creative ways of continuing our traditions. While this video in no way replaces the hugs and well wishes that we would normally convey, we are hoping that in some way that this celebrates the career and fun memories that we have shared. Congratulations to Cindy, Ray, Laurie, and Veronica on your retirement, you will all be missed!
#CrookstonPirates

post_text:
Good news! Yearbook signing IS NOT canceled!

Yearbook Signing (Socially Distanced Edition):
We are excited to announce that the Crookston High School Optimist yearbook signing tradition is alive and it‚Äôs fully digital to suit our socially distanced students.

Jostens has just launched a new platform, Yearbook Digital Signing Pages, that gives every student in our school the chance to create virtual signing pages, invite their friends to leave messages, and print out the final pages to keep with the yearbook as a permanent keepsake.This is free for every student whether they purchased a yearbook or not.

Share the link below with your student so they can get started with their yearbook signing.
yearbooksigning.jostens.com
#CrookstonPirates

Students will need to drive up to the WEST doors of the school and text 289-2569 or 280-4021. When you arrive, your order will be delivered to you curbside. You will need to pick up food at 5:30 pm.
It is very IMPORTANT to be on time as we don't have freezer space and need to move the frozen food as quick as possible.

Any questions please call 289-2569 Theresa Tahran

post_text: Crookston Public Schools FREE MEAL SERVICE during emergency school closure due to COVID-19:
text: Crookston Public Schools FREE MEAL SERVICE during emergency school closure due to COVID-19:

post_text: Highland Elementary School will be accepting donations of non-perishable food items and gift cards from WalMart, Hugos, local restaurants, cash cards for families in need during this time of school closure. If you would like to donate non-perishable food items please bring them to door 6 to be buzzed into the building. Please place your donations along the wall away from the door. We would like to try to continue to keep social distancing in place as much as possible so please do not enter the school or office unless you have a gift card to donate that you are not comfortable leaving in the hallway. If you are concerned at all about getting through this time at home with your family please contact Tara Rodriguez 701-740-4473 or Jessica Shockman 218-289-7023.

It's our first of many Faculty Friday posts! Today we are going to get to know Jana Hodgson:

"I have been an Administrative Assistant at Highland Elementary School for almost 8 years. I graduated with a Bachelors Degree in Business Administration emphasis Marketing and a minor in Information Technology from the University of Minnesota, Crookston.

I have been working in Customer Service or Sales my entire working life. I am married to my husband of almost 18 years, Nathaniel. We have two children: Damian, a Crookston graduate who is a freshman at Minnesota State University, Moorhead and Delta, a 2nd Grader at Highland Elementary School.

I enjoy movies, going to my children's events, reading, and laughing. I love working for Crookston Public Schools because of the kids. They are so much fun to be around every day."

#CrookstonPirates #FacultyFriday

Crookston High School senior Blaine Asman auditioned and WAS SELECTED as Tenor II for the 2019-2020 Minnesota Music Educator‚Äôs Association All-State Men‚Äôs Chorus.
